PART 1: CORE PLATFORM WORKFLOWS

1. User Authentication & Multi-tenancy Workflow

User Registration Flow:
  Step 1: User visits company career site with widget
  Step 2: Clicks "Apply Now" ‚Üí Widget modal opens
  Step 3: Registration options:
    Option A: New Applicant
      ‚Üí Enter email, password
      ‚Üí Verify email (OTP)
      ‚Üí Create basic profile
      ‚Üí Redirect to application
    Option B: Existing Applicant
      ‚Üí Login with email/password
      ‚Üí Redirect to application
    Option C: Social Login
      ‚Üí Login with Google/LinkedIn
      ‚Üí Import profile data (optional)
      ‚Üí Complete missing fields
  Step 4: Multi-tenancy isolation
    - Each user belongs to tenant (company)
    - Data scoped to tenant
    - Shared applicants across company locations

Login Flow:
  Step 1: Enter credentials
  Step 2: System validates
  Step 3: Check MFA (if enabled)
  Step 4: Load user context + permissions
  Step 5: Redirect to appropriate dashboard

Security Flow:
  - JWT tokens for API
  - Cookie authentication for web
  - Rate limiting per IP/user
  - Failed login tracking
  - Account lockout after 5 attempts

2. Applicant Profile Management Workflow

Profile Creation Wizard:
  Step 1: Personal Information
    - Name, contact details, address
    - Demographic data (optional, EEO)
    - Save & Continue

  Step 2: Employment Preferences
    - Desired job types, locations
    - Salary expectations
    - Availability
    - Save & Continue

  Step 3: Work History
    - Add past employment (multiple)
    - Import from LinkedIn
    - Upload resume (auto-parse)
    - Save & Continue

  Step 4: Education & Skills
    - Educational background
    - Certifications, licenses
    - Skills inventory
    - Save & Continue

  Step 5: Documents
    - Resume upload (PDF, DOC)
    - Cover letter templates
    - Portfolio links
    - Reference contacts
    - Complete Profile

Profile Updates:
  - Real-time auto-save
  - Version history
  - Export profile (PDF/JSON)
  - Privacy controls (what companies see)

3. Job Posting Management Workflow

Job Creation Flow (Company HR):
  Step 1: Basic Information
    - Job title, department
    - Location(s) (single or multiple)
    - Employment type (Full-time, Part-time, etc.)
    - Save as draft

  Step 2: Job Details
    - Rich text description
    - Responsibilities, requirements
    - Salary range (optional)
    - Benefits information
    - Save draft

  Step 3: Application Settings
    - Custom questions (add from library)
    - Required documents
    - Assessment requirements
    - Application deadline
    - Save draft

  Step 4: Review & Publish
    - Preview job posting
    - Check compliance (EEO, etc.)
    - Set status: Draft, Active, Closed
    - Publish to widget/career site

Job Approval Flow (if multi-level):
  - HR creates ‚Üí Manager approves ‚Üí System publishes
  - Notification to approver
  - SLA for approval (24 hours)
  - Escalation if delayed

4. Application Submission Workflow

Standard Application Flow:
  Step 1: Job Discovery
    - Browse jobs on widget
    - Search/filter by role, location
    - View job details
    - Click "Apply"

  Step 2: Account Check
    - If logged in ‚Üí proceed
    - If not logged in ‚Üí redirect to login/register
    - Return to application after auth

  Step 3: Pre-fill Application
    - Auto-fill from profile
    - Review and edit information
    - Upload additional documents
    - Save progress (can continue later)

  Step 4: Custom Questions
    - Answer company-specific questions
    - Required vs optional indicators
    - Character counters for text
    - File uploads if needed

  Step 5: Review & Submit
    - Summary page (all answers)
    - Edit any section
    - Terms and conditions
    - Digital signature
    - Submit application

  Step 6: Confirmation
    - Application ID generated
    - Email confirmation sent
    - Status tracker shown
    - QR code for tracking

QR Code Application Flow:
  - Scan QR code at job location
  - Deep link to specific job
  - Skip job discovery step
  - Track source as "QR Code"

5. Company Administration Workflow

Company Setup Flow:
  Step 1: Registration
    - Company admin signs up
    - Enter company details
    - Choose subscription plan
    - Payment (if paid plan)
    - Create admin account

  Step 2: Basic Configuration
    - Upload logo
    - Set brand colors
    - Configure email templates
    - Set up locations

  Step 3: Team Management
    - Invite HR team members
    - Assign roles/permissions
    - Set up approval workflows
    - Configure notifications

  Step 4: Widget Setup
    - Generate embed code
    - Customize widget appearance
    - Test on staging site
    - Deploy to production

Daily HR Workflow:
  Step 1: Dashboard Review
    - New applications count
    - Urgent actions needed
    - Analytics overview

  Step 2: Application Review
    - Filter applications (new, by job, by location)
    - View applicant profiles
    - Review answers to custom questions
    - Download resumes/documents

  Step 3: Status Management
    - Change application status:
      Received ‚Üí Screening ‚Üí Interview ‚Üí Offer ‚Üí Hired
      Or: Rejected ‚Üí Archived
    - Add internal notes
    - Assign to team members

  Step 4: Communication
    - Send templated emails
    - Schedule interviews
    - Request additional information
    - Send rejection/offer letters

6. Widget System Workflow

Widget Generation Flow:
  Step 1: Company admin logs in
  Step 2: Navigates to Widget settings
  Step 3: Customize appearance:
    - Colors (primary, secondary)
    - Fonts
    - Logo
    - Layout options
  Step 4: Configure behavior:
    - Job display options
    - Search filters
    - Application flow steps
  Step 5: Generate embed code:
    - JavaScript snippet
    - Iframe option
    - Direct link option
  Step 6: Test widget:
    - Preview in sandbox
    - Test application flow
    - Check mobile responsiveness
  Step 7: Deploy:
    - Copy embed code
    - Add to career site
    - Verify installation

Widget Runtime Flow (on career site):
  1. Load widget JavaScript
  2. Authenticate with platform API
  3. Fetch company jobs
  4. Render job listings
  5. Handle user interactions
  6. Open application modal
  7. Post application to platform
  8. Show confirmation

7. Basic Analytics Workflow

Data Collection Flow:
  - Track all user interactions
  - Application submissions
  - Job views/clicks
  - Source tracking (QR, widget, direct)
  - Time spent metrics
  - Conversion funnel data

Reporting Flow:
  Step 1: Data aggregation (daily batch)
  Step 2: Generate metrics:
    - Applications per job
    - Time to hire
    - Source effectiveness
    - Applicant demographics (EEO)
  Step 3: Dashboard display
  Step 4: Export reports (CSV, PDF)
  Step 5: Schedule automated reports

Alert Workflow:
  - Monitor key metrics
  - Threshold alerts (e.g., low applications)
  - SLA breaches (e.g., slow review)
  - System health alerts

PART 2: COMMERCIAL EXTENSION WORKFLOWS

8. Assessment Builder Platform Workflow

Assessment Creation Flow:
  Step 1: Create New Assessment
    - Name, description, type
    - Time limit, passing score
    - Proctoring settings

  Step 2: Question Design
    - Add questions from library or create new
    - Question types: MC, text, video, file, coding
    - Set points, required/optional
    - Add answer choices (for MC)

  Step 3: Assessment Structure
    - Organize into sections
    - Set section time limits
    - Randomize question order
    - Add branching logic

  Step 4: Settings & Branding
    - Company branding
    - Instructions, messages
    - Result visibility (show score, answers)
    - Retake policy

  Step 5: Assign & Publish
    - Assign to specific jobs
    - Set schedule (available dates)
    - Publish assessment
    - Share link with applicants

Applicant Taking Flow:
  Step 1: Receive invitation
  Step 2: Identity verification (if proctored)
  Step 3: Take assessment
  Step 4: Auto-save progress
  Step 5: Submit for grading
  Step 6: View results (if allowed)

Grading Workflow:
  - Auto-grade multiple choice
  - Manual grading queue for text/video
  - Multiple graders (for consistency)
  - Final score calculation
  - Results notification

9. Advanced Analytics & Reporting Workflow

Data Pipeline:
  Step 1: Raw data collection
    - Application events
    - User interactions
    - System metrics
    - External data (job boards)

  Step 2: Data processing
    - Clean and normalize
    - Enrich with external data
    - Calculate derived metrics
    - Store in analytics database

  Step 3: Analysis
    - Funnel analysis (apply ‚Üí hire)
    - Time series analysis
    - Cohort analysis
    - Predictive modeling

  Step 4: Visualization
    - Interactive dashboards
    - Custom report builder
    - Scheduled reports
    - Export to BI tools

Advanced Reports:
  - Diversity & Inclusion dashboard
  - Cost-per-hire analysis
  - Quality-of-hire tracking
  - Competitor benchmarking
  - Market intelligence

10. White-label Branding Workflow

Branding Setup Flow:
  Step 1: Company purchases white-label license
  Step 2: Access white-label dashboard
  Step 3: Upload branding assets:
    - Logo (multiple sizes)
    - Favicon
    - Color palette
    - Fonts
    - Custom CSS

  Step 4: Configure domains:
    - Custom subdomain (careers.company.com)
    - Or full custom domain
    - SSL certificate setup (auto)

  Step 5: Customize content:
    - Terms of service
    - Privacy policy
    - Email templates
    - Page copy

  Step 6: Preview & Test:
    - Preview on staging
    - Test on multiple devices
    - Check email templates
    - Approve branding

  Step 7: Go Live:
    - DNS configuration
    - Certificate issuance
    - Final testing
    - Switch traffic

White-label Features:
  - No UJAS branding anywhere
  - Custom email domains
  - Branded mobile apps (optional)
  - Custom app store listings

11. Enterprise Integration Workflow

Integration Types:
  1. HRIS Integration (Workday, SAP, etc.)
  2. ATS Integration (Greenhouse, Lever)
  3. Background Check (Checkr, Sterling)
  4. Single Sign-On (SAML, OIDC)
  5. Calendar (Google, Outlook)
  6. Communication (Slack, Teams)

Integration Setup Flow:
  Step 1: Purchase integration license
  Step 2: Access integration dashboard
  Step 3: Choose integration type
  Step 4: Configure connection:
    - API keys/tokens
    - Webhook endpoints
    - Authentication method
  Step 5: Map data fields:
    - Applicant data mapping
    - Job data sync
    - Status synchronization
  Step 6: Test integration:
    - Test data sync
    - Verify webhooks
    - Check error handling
  Step 7: Go Live:
    - Enable integration
    - Monitor initial sync
    - Train users

Sync Workflow (Example: HRIS):
  - Real-time or batch sync
  - Applicant data ‚Üí HRIS
  - Job data ‚Üê HRIS
  - Status updates bidirectional
  - Error handling and retry

12. Marketplace System Workflow

Developer Flow:
  Step 1: Register as developer
  Step 2: Create plugin/extension
  Step 3: Submit for review:
    - Security scan
    - Compatibility test
    - Quality check
  Step 4: Set pricing:
    - Free or paid
    - One-time or subscription
    - Trial period
  Step 5: Publish to marketplace
  Step 6: Manage updates, support

Customer Purchase Flow:
  Step 1: Browse marketplace
  Step 2: View plugin details
  Step 3: Purchase/install:
    - Add to cart
    - Checkout
    - Payment processing
    - Automatic installation
  Step 4: Configure plugin
  Step 5: Use in platform

Revenue Distribution Flow:
  Step 1: Customer payment
  Step 2: Platform fee (30%) deducted
  Step 3: Developer payout (70%)
  Step 4: Monthly payout to developers
  Step 5: Tax documentation (1099, etc.)

PART 3: DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOWS

13. Plugin Development Workflow

Plugin Architecture:
  - Core platform provides interfaces
  - Plugins implement interfaces
  - Dependency injection for plugins
  - Database migration support
  - Asset management (JS, CSS, images)

Development Flow:
  Step 1: Set up development environment
    - Clone plugin template
    - Install dependencies
    - Configure local testing

  Step 2: Implement plugin logic
    - Business logic
    - Database models
    - API endpoints
    - UI components

  Step 3: Testing
    - Unit tests
    - Integration tests
    - UI tests
    - Performance tests

  Step 4: Packaging
    - Create manifest file
    - Bundle assets
    - Create installer
    - Version tagging

  Step 5: Submission
    - Submit to marketplace
    - Security review
    - Quality review
    - Approval process

14. Contribution Workflow (Open Source)

Fork & Clone Flow:
  1. Fork repository on GitHub
  2. Clone locally
  3. Create feature branch
  4. Make changes
  5. Test changes
  6. Commit with conventional commits

Pull Request Flow:
  1. Push to GitHub
  2. Create pull request
  3. Automated checks:
     - Build passes
     - Tests pass
     - Code coverage
     - Linting
  4. Manual review:
     - Code review
     - Design review
     - Security review
  5. Merge to main
  6. Deploy to staging

Release Flow:
  1. Create release branch
  2. Update version numbers
  3. Update changelog
  4. Build release artifacts
  5. Create GitHub release
  6. Deploy to production
  7. Announce to community

15. Release Management Workflow

Release Schedule:
  - Weekly: Patch releases (bug fixes)
  - Monthly: Minor releases (features)
  - Quarterly: Major releases (breaking changes)

Release Process:
  Step 1: Feature Freeze
    - No new features
    - Only bug fixes
    - 1 week before release

  Step 2: Release Candidate
    - Build RC
    - Deploy to staging
    - Community testing
    - Bug fixes

  Step 3: Final Release
    - Build final version
    - Update documentation
    - Release notes
    - Announcement

  Step 4: Deployment
    - Deploy to production
    - Monitor metrics
    - Handle rollback if needed

16. Quality Assurance Workflow

Testing Pyramid:
  Layer 1: Unit Tests (70%)
    - Business logic
    - Services
    - Utilities

  Layer 2: Integration Tests (20%)
    - API endpoints
    - Database operations
    - External integrations

  Layer 3: E2E Tests (10%)
    - Critical user journeys
    - Cross-browser testing
    - Performance testing

Automated Testing Flow:
  1. Code commit triggers CI
  2. Run unit tests
  3. Run integration tests
  4. Run E2E tests
  5. Generate coverage report
  6. Security scan
  7. Performance benchmark

Manual Testing Flow:
  1. Test new features
  2. Regression testing
  3. Usability testing
  4. Accessibility testing
  5. Cross-device testing

