17. Sales & Onboarding Workflow

Free Tier Onboarding:
  Step 1: Sign up for free account
  Step 2: Verify email
  Step 3: Quick setup wizard
  Step 4: Get widget code
  Step 5: Add to website
  Step 6: Welcome email sequence
  Step 7: Usage monitoring
  Step 8: Upgrade prompts at limits

Paid Tier Onboarding:
  Step 1: Sales consultation
  Step 2: Choose plan
  Step 3: Payment processing
  Step 4: Account setup
  Step 5: Implementation call
  Step 6: Data migration (if needed)
  Step 7: Training sessions
  Step 8: Go-live support
  Step 9: Regular check-ins

Enterprise Sales Flow:
  Step 1: Discovery call
  Step 2: Proposal
  Step 3: Contract negotiation
  Step 4: Security review
  Step 5: Legal approval
  Step 6: Implementation planning
  Step 7: Custom development (if needed)
  Step 8: Deployment
  Step 9: Training
  Step 10: Account management

18. Customer Support Workflow

Support Tiers:
  Tier 1: Community Support (Free)
    - Forums
    - Documentation
    - Community help

  Tier 2: Email Support (Pro)
    - 24-hour response time
    - Business hours
    - Ticket system

  Tier 3: Priority Support (Business)
    - 4-hour response time
    - Phone support
    - Dedicated support agent

  Tier 4: Enterprise Support
    - 1-hour response time
    - 24/7 phone support
    - Dedicated account manager
    - On-site support available

Support Ticket Flow:
  1. Customer submits ticket
  2. Auto-categorization
  3. Assignment to support agent
  4. Investigation
  5. Resolution
  6. Customer satisfaction survey
  7. Ticket closure

Knowledge Base Flow:
  1. Identify common issues
  2. Create documentation
  3. Review by SMEs
  4. Publish to knowledge base
  5. Monitor usage
  6. Update based on feedback

19. Revenue Distribution Workflow

Monthly Revenue Cycle:
  Step 1: Collect revenue
    - SaaS subscriptions
    - Plugin sales
    - Service fees
  Step 2: Calculate payouts
    - Platform share (30%)
    - Developer shares (70%)
    - Affiliate commissions
  Step 3: Process payouts
    - Generate payment reports
    - Transfer to developers
    - Tax documentation
  Step 4: Financial reporting
    - Revenue reports
    - Expense tracking
    - Profit/Loss statements
  Step 5: Tax compliance
    - Sales tax collection
    - Income tax reporting
    - International tax compliance

Developer Payout Flow:
  1. Monthly sales report
  2. Minimum threshold check ($50)
  3. Generate payout batch
  4. Transfer via Stripe Connect
  5. Email notification to developer
  6. Tax form generation (year-end)

